org.nd4j.linalg.dataset.api.iterator

Interface MultiDataSetIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<MultiDataSet>, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ParallelMultiDataSetIterator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsyncMultiDataSetIterator, AsyncShieldMultiDataSetIterator, BenchmarkMultiDataSetIterator, EarlyTerminationMultiDataSetIterator, FileMultiDataSetIterator, IteratorMultiDataSetIterator, JointMultiDataSetIterator, MultiDataSetIteratorAdapter, MultiDataSetLoaderIterator, PathSparkMultiDataSetIterator, PortableDataStreamMultiDataSetIterator, RandomMultiDataSetIterator, RecordReaderMultiDataSetIterator, SingletonMultiDataSetIterator, SparkAMDSI, TestMultiDataSetIterator, VirtualMultiDataSetIterator

    public interface MultiDataSetIterator
extends java.util.Iterator<MultiDataSet>, java.io.Serializable
    An iterator for MultiDataSet objects. Typical usage is for machine learning algorithms with multiple independent input (features) and output (labels) arrays.

      • asyncSupported

        boolean asyncSupported()
        Does this MultiDataSetIterator support asynchronous prefetching of multiple MultiDataSet objects? Most MultiDataSetIterators do, but in some cases it may not make sense to wrap this iterator in an iterator that does asynchronous prefetching. For example, it would not make sense to use asynchronous prefetching for the following types of iterators: (a) Iterators that store their full contents in memory already (b) Iterators that re-use features/labels arrays (as future next() calls will overwrite past contents) (c) Iterators that already implement some level of asynchronous prefetching (d) Iterators that may return different data depending on when the next() method is called
        Returns:
        true if asynchronous prefetching from this iterator is OK; false if asynchronous prefetching should not be used with this iterator

        void reset()
        Resets the iterator back to the beginning
